= class GLib::FilterInputStream

== Object Hierarchy

* Object
  * GLib::Instantiatable
    * GLib::Object
      * GLib::InputStream
        * GLib::FilterInputStream

== Instance Methods

--- base_stream

    Gets the underlying base stream on which the io ops will be done.
     * Returns: The underlying base stream on which the io ops will be done

--- close_base_stream=(close_base_stream)

    Sets the value if the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed.
     * close_base_stream: true if the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed
     * Returns: close_base_stream

--- close_base_stream?

    Gets the value if the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed.
     * Returns: true if the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed

--- set_close_base_stream(close_base_stream)

    Same as close_base_stream=.
     * close_base_stream: true if the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed
     * Returns: self

== Properties

--- base-stream: GInputStream (Read/Write)

    The underlying base stream on which the io ops will be done.

--- close-base-stream: true or false (Read/Write)

    If the base stream should be closed when the filter stream is closed.

